span.strong:
NSHS students get a real college experience – virtually – during the COVID-19 school closures.
Our students are not missing important instruction time.
Fall 2020 registration is now open to current juniors and seniors!

div.h3: Get a head start on your college degree while still in high school!
div.p: Nevada State High School is a tuition-free, public, early college charter high school for 11th and 12th graders.

ul.li: NSHS students take real college classes that count for both high school and college credit.

Save thousands in college tuition as attending NSHS is absolutely FREE! We pay for your
tuition and fees for up to 5 college classes.
NSHS’s proven process successfully helps students transition to college personally, academically, and socially.

div.div:
“I have many reasons why NSHS has been an amazing fit for my daughter. She was bullied in middle school and then placed in a online home school program. I was looking for opportunities that would supply various values for my daughter and NSHS provides those for us.
She has always been one that is focused on her education and getting ahead in life. Seeing that this school provides an opportunity to get a jump start on her college career was amazing. It also provides the life skills that are needed that traditional schools no longer provide. For example budget planning, resume and interview skills, applying for scholarships, being active by volunteering and having the student engage in social events.
She has excelled in all her classes, found friendships and the staff is beyond caring. They are willing to give a helping hand and guide the students to the right decisions. They make themselves available willing and eager to help.
This school is truly amazing and thankful for John and Wendi Hawk for having a vision to bring a quality program to our community.”

“When I heard about Nevada State High School, I was excited about what was being offered to students, but at the same time I was extremely worried that my daughter would not have the “high school experience” that traditional high schools offer. That notwithstanding, my daughter and I decided to proceed with the application process and see where it took her. When my daughter was accepted, she made the final decision to transfer to NSHS. Approximately 6 months into her journey with NSHS, I asked her if she made the right decision to attend NSHS. My daughter said this, “It was the best decision that I have ever made for myself. The program is tough, but it has pushed me to be a better student and believe in myself.” NSHS has given my daughter opportunities that no other school has offered to her. Her academic resume is quite impressive and she has already been accepted to a university.
Thank you NSHS for giving my daughter a head start into her college career!”

div.div:
We are still accepting new student registrations and have shifted our registration process to be 100% virtual during the COVID-19 school closures. Fall 2020 registration is still currently open for current 10th and 11th graders!
Register now!
Want more information? We will be hosting our open house informational meetings virtually using Zoom, a video conferencing app, until further notice. Please sign-up below to attend. Information on how to join the virtual open house will be emailed to you after you sign up.
Upcoming Dates and Times:
Friday, April 17th, 2020 at 4pm
SIGN UP

Thank you so much for your interest in Nevada State High School! Fall 2020 registration opens February 1st, 2020 for students that will be entering their junior or senior year for the 2020-2021 School Year.
Juniors = entering their 3rd year with 11+ credits
Seniors = entering their 4th year with 17+ credits
Please fill out this form to RSVP for upcoming open houses and to be added to our contact list for Fall 2020 registration.
